<StaticPageLayout
  title="Editorial policy"
  description="How evidique separates evidence, opinion, commercial relationships, corrections, and demonstration content."
  kicker="The rules behind the verdict"
>
  <p><strong>Effective July 11, 2026.</strong> Ethan Miller owns and applies this policy.</p>
  <h2>Evidence before adjectives</h2><p>
    We tie important claims to a task, screenshot, output, primary source, or dated observation. We
    label research-only work and never present it as hands-on testing.
  </p>
  <h2>Editorial control</h2><p>
    Editors choose topics, tasks, scoring, conclusions, and corrections. Vendors may flag factual
    errors but do not preview or approve verdicts.
  </p>
  <h2>Demonstration pages</h2><p>
    MVP samples carry a prominent notice. Their placeholder scores and conclusions are not
    recommendations and should never be promoted as finished reviews.
  </p>
  <h2>Corrections</h2><p>
    We verify specific correction requests, update material errors promptly, and change the visible
    updated date. Significant changes should include an editor's note.
  </p>
</StaticPageLayout>
